{{Politics of Burundi}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Burundi]] on 18 November 1981. The new constitution would make the country a [[presidential system|presidential]] republic with a [[unicameralism|unicameral]] [[National Assembly of Burundi|National Assembly]], as well as creating a [[one-party state]] with the [[Union for National Progress]] as the sole legal party. It was supported by 99.28% of voters with a 94% turnout.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/bi.html Elections in Burundi] African Elections Database</ref>
